        "qa": "Q. How long should you use Teeth Guard 0.2% Mouth Wash?::: The duration of use of Teeth Guard 0.2% Mouth Wash will depend on the condition it is being prescribed for. If you are using it for gum disease (gingivitis) it may be used for a month. If being used for mouth ulcers and thrush, this mouthwash may be used till 2 days after the symptoms are relieved.| Q. Does Teeth Guard 0.2% Mouth Wash stain teeth?::: Yes, though it does not occur in everyone, Teeth Guard 0.2% Mouth Wash may stain your teeth and tongue. Staining is not permanent and may disappear after discontinuation of treatment. Brushing the teeth with regular toothpaste before using Teeth Guard 0.2% Mouth Wash can prevent staining. You should also avoid tannin-containing food and drinks such as tea and coffee.| Q. Does Teeth Guard 0.2% Mouth Wash help bad breath?::: Yes, Teeth Guard 0.2% Mouth Wash is effective in reducing bad breath, which persists for about 3 hours. However, the risk of staining teeth and alteration of taste should be borne in mind before you start using it. Also, use this medicine judiciously.| Q. How should Teeth Guard 0.2% Mouth Wash be used?::: It should be used as required. It is generally used twice daily. Rinse the mouth thoroughly for about 1 minute with 10 ml of Teeth Guard 0.2% Mouth Wash mouthwash. After rinsing, expel it from your mouth.| Q. What precautions should be followed while using Teeth Guard 0.2% Mouth Wash?::: Using toothpastes immediately after the mouthwash may interfere with the working of mouthwash properly. Use it before the mouthwash or at a different time of the day. Always rinse your mouth before using the mouthwash.| Q. How long should you use Teeth Guard 0.2% Mouth Wash?::: The duration of use of Teeth Guard 0.2% Mouth Wash will depend on the condition it is being prescribed for. If you are using it for gum disease (gingivitis) it may be used for a month. If being used for mouth ulcers and thrush, this mouthwash may be used till 2 days after the symptoms are relieved.| Q. Does Teeth Guard 0.2% Mouth Wash stain teeth?::: Yes, though it does not occur in everyone, Teeth Guard 0.2% Mouth Wash may stain your teeth and tongue. Staining is not permanent and may disappear after discontinuation of treatment. Brushing the teeth with regular toothpaste before using Teeth Guard 0.2% Mouth Wash can prevent staining. You should also avoid tannin-containing food and drinks such as tea and coffee.| Q. Does Teeth Guard 0.2% Mouth Wash help bad breath?::: Yes, Teeth Guard 0.2% Mouth Wash is effective in reducing bad breath, which persists for about 3 hours. However, the risk of staining teeth and alteration of taste should be borne in mind before you start using it. Also, use this medicine judiciously.| Q. How should Teeth Guard 0.2% Mouth Wash be used?::: It should be used as required. It is generally used twice daily. Rinse the mouth thoroughly for about 1 minute with 10 ml of Teeth Guard 0.2% Mouth Wash mouthwash. After rinsing, expel it from your mouth.| Q. What precautions should be followed while using Teeth Guard 0.2% Mouth Wash?::: Using toothpastes immediately after the mouthwash may interfere with the working of mouthwash properly. Use it before the mouthwash or at a different time of the day. Always rinse your mouth before using the mouthwash.",
