        "qa": "Q. What organisms does Gracef 250mg Injection cover?::: Gracef 250mg Injection is active against pseudomonas, anaerobes, and staphylococcus bacteria. It may not be effective against methicillin- resistant Staphylococcus aureus (MRSA).| Q. How is Gracef 250mg Injection administered?::: Gracef 250mg Injection is administered under the supervision of a trained healthcare professional or a doctor and should not be self administered. The dose will depend on the condition you are being treated for and will be decided by your doctor. Follow your doctor’s instructions carefully to get maximum benefit from Gracef 250mg Injection.| Q. Can the use of Gracef 250mg Injection cause diarrhea?::: Yes, the use of Gracef 250mg Injection can cause diarrhea. Gracef 250mg Injection is an antibiotic which kills the harmful bacteria. However, it also affects the helpful bacteria in your stomach or intestine and causes diarrhea. If diarrhea persists, talk to your doctor about it.| Q. How long does Gracef 250mg Injection take to work?::: Usually, Gracef 250mg Injection starts working soon after you take it. However, it may take some days to kill all the harmful bacteria and relieve your symptoms completely.| Q. What if I do not get better after using Gracef 250mg Injection?::: Inform your doctor if you do not feel better even after finishing the full course of treatment. You must also inform your doctor if the symptoms get worse while using this medicine.| Q. Is Gracef 250mg Injection effective?::: Gracef 250mg Injection is effective if used in the dose and duration advised by your doctor. Do not stop taking it even if you see improvement in your condition. If you stop using Gracef 250mg Injection too early, the symptoms may return or worsen.",
