        "qa": "Q. What happens if I stop taking Valdiv ER 250 Tablet?::: You should not stop taking Valdiv ER 250 Tablet without consulting your doctor. The dose of Valdiv ER 250 Tablet should be reduced gradually and eventually can be stopped under the supervision of a doctor or specialist. Suddenly stopping the medication may lead to recurrence of symptoms or irritability, anxiety, dizziness and tremors.| Q. Is Valdiv ER 250 Tablet a mood stabilizer?::: Yes, Valdiv ER 250 Tablet can sometimes be used as a mood stabilizer. It is given in patients who experience rapid changes in their mood. It works by calming the hyperactivity of the brain during mood changes.| Q. Can Valdiv ER 250 Tablet cause weight gain?::: Yes, Valdiv ER 250 Tablet may cause weight gain. The gain in weight could be due to an increase in hunger. Keep a check on your diet and exercise regularly to prevent any weight gain. If you are have concerns related to weight gain, consult your doctor.| Q. Does Valdiv ER 250 Tablet make you sleepy?::: Yes, Valdiv ER 250 Tablet may make you feel sleepy. Avoid driving or other work that requires mental focus until you know how it affects you.| Q. Does Valdiv ER 250 Tablet cause hair loss?::: Yes, Valdiv ER 250 Tablet may cause hair loss. However, it is only for a short time and is usually dose related. Please consult your doctor if the hair loss bothers you or persists for a longer duration.| Q. Can Valdiv ER 250 Tablet damage my liver?::: Yes, Valdiv ER 250 Tablet can cause damage to the liver. The risk is more likely to occur during the first 6 months of starting the treatment with Valdiv ER 250 Tablet. Symptoms of liver damage may include nausea or vomiting, loss of appetite, stomach pain, dark coloured urine, facial swelling, yellowing of the skin or white of eyes. Therefore, it is important to have liver function tests done before starting the medicine and. Tests should be done periodically during the first 6 months of therapy, especially in those who are likely to be at risk and those with a prior history of liver disease.| Q. Can I take alcohol while I am taking Valdiv ER 250 Tablet?::: Avoid alcohol consumption while you are on treatment with Valdiv ER 250 Tablet. Taking alcohol with this medicine may make you feel more drowsy, light headed or dizzy.| Q. What are the laboratory tests recommended prior to taking Valdiv ER 250 Tablet?::: The doctor may suggest blood tests before starting the treatment with Valdiv ER 250 Tablet. The tests may include blood cell count, including platelet count, bleeding time and coagulation tests These tests are also advised to avoid any spontaneous bruising or bleeding. In addition to this, liver function tests are advised before therapy. It is recommended to periodically monitor liver function during the first 6 months of therapy, primarily in those who seem most at risk and those with a prior history of liver disease.| Q. What should be done if I start experiencing abdominal pain, nausea and anorexia?::: If you experience acute severe abdominal pain along with nausea and vomiting, it may be due to pancreatitis. Immediately consult your doctor in case you experience these symptoms. Your doctor may get your levels of serum amylase checked. In case the test shows positive results for pancreatitis, the medication should be stopped immediately.| Q. How to check for overdose of Valdiv ER 250 Tablet?::: Overdose of Valdiv ER 250 Tablet may cause headaches, blurred eyesight due to pupils of the eyes becoming smaller, lack of reflexes, confusion and tiredness. You may also experience weak or “floppy” muscles, fits (seizures), loss of consciousness, behavioral changes and breathing difficulties such as fast breathing, shortness of breath, or chest pain. Immediate medical assistance is required in case of overdose.",
