        "safety_advise": "- Alcohol : UNSAFE  It is unsafe to consume alcohol with Betagesic 650mg Tablet. | - Pregnancy : CONSULT YOUR DOCTOR  Betagesic 650mg Tablet may be unsafe to use during pregnancy. Although there are limited studies in humans, animal studies have shown harmful effects on the developing baby. Your doctor will weigh the benefits and any potential risks before prescribing it to you. Please consult your doctor. | - Breast feeding : SAFE IF PRESCRIBED  Betagesic 650mg Tablet is safe to use during breastfeeding. Human studies suggest that the drug does not pass into the breastmilk in a significant amount and is not harmful to the baby. | - Driving : SAFE  Betagesic 650mg Tablet does not usually affect your ability to drive. | - Kidney : CAUTION  Betagesic 650mg Tablet should be used with caution in patients with kidney disease. Dose adjustment of Betagesic 650mg Tablet may be needed. Please consult your doctor.However, Betagesic 650mg Tablet contains paracetamol which is considered the safest painkiller for kidney disease patients. | - Liver : CAUTION  Betagesic 650mg Tablet should be used with caution in patients with liver disease. Dose adjustment of Betagesic 650mg Tablet may be needed. Please consult your doctor.However, the use of Betagesic 650mg Tablet is not recommended in patients with severe liver disease and active liver disease.",
        "if_miss": "If you miss a dose of Betagesic 650mg Tablet, take it as soon as possible. However, if it is almost time for your next dose, skip the missed dose and go back to your regular schedule. Do not double the dose.",
