        "qa": "Q. What if I vomit after taking Betagesic 650mg Tablet?::: If you vomit in less than 30 minutes after having a dose of Betagesic 650mg Tablet tablets or syrup, retake the same dose again. If you vomit after 30 minutes of a dose, you do not need to take another one until the next standard dose.| Q. When will I feel better after taking the Betagesic 650mg Tablet?::: Usually, you will start feeling better after about half an hour of taking a Betagesic 650mg Tablet.| Q. How often can I take the Betagesic 650mg Tablet?::: You should only take four doses of Betagesic 650mg Tablet in 24 hours. There should be a gap of at least 4 hours between two doses. Do not take Betagesic 650mg Tablet for more than 3 days without consulting a doctor first.| Q. Does Betagesic 650mg Tablet make babies sleepy?::: No, Betagesic 650mg Tablet does not make babies sleepy. It is a pain-relieving medicine that is also used to control high fever.| Q. Is Betagesic 650mg Tablet safe for children?::: Betagesic 650mg Tablet is considered safe for children only when used as directed by the doctor.| Q. Is Betagesic 650mg Tablet an antibiotic?::: No, Betagesic 650mg Tablet is not an antibiotic. It works as a painkiller and fever-reducing medicine.| Q. Can I take Betagesic 650mg Tablet and ibuprofen together?::: Ibuprofen and Betagesic 650mg Tablet are safe medicines, but both should not be used together. Consult your doctor if you are not sure.| Q. How long does a Betagesic 650mg Tablet take to work?::: Betagesic 650mg Tablet takes around 30-45 min to start working and show its effects. It is advised to take this medicine for the duration suggested by the doctor. Consult your doctor if you experience any bothersome side effects.| Q. What are the serious side effects of taking an excess of the Betagesic 650mg Tablet?::: Overdose of Betagesic 650mg Tablete may cause severe life-threatening liver injury. Taking more than the prescribed dose may also cause kidney injury, decreased platelet count, and even coma. Early symptoms of an overdose include nausea, vomiting, and general tiredness. Immediately consult a doctor or reach an emergency in case of a suspected overdose.| Q. Can Betagesic 650mg Tablet cause nausea and vomiting?::: Yes, Betagesic 650mg Tablet may cause nausea and vomiting. Taking it with milk, food or antacids can prevent nausea. Avoid taking fatty or fried foods along with this medication. In case of vomiting, drink plenty of water or other fluids by taking small frequent sips. Talk to your doctor if vomiting persists and you notice signs of dehydration, like dark colored and strong-smelling urine or a low frequency of urination. Do not take any other medicines without speaking to your doctor.| Q. Is Betagesic 650mg Tablet helpful in relieving stomach pain due to indigestion?::: No, Betagesic 650mg Tablet should not be taken for stomach pain without consulting a doctor. This drug can increase stomach acid secretion which may aggravate an unknown underlying condition.| Q. Can I take Betagesic 650mg Tablet with an antibiotic?::: Yes, taking Betagesic 650mg Tablet and antibiotics at the same time should not cause any problems. Antibiotics are used to help clear infections but often don't do anything to relieve pain. Therefore you can generally take Betagesic 650mg Tablet alongside your antibiotics. However, always consult your doctor before taking any medications.",
