        "manufacturer_address": "Orchid Towers', #313, Valluvar Kottam High Road, Nungambakkam, Chennai - 600 034, Tamil Nadu, India",
        "qa": "Q. Why is Alzepil 5mg Tablet taken at night?::: Alzepil 5mg Tablet is recommended to be taken before going to bed to reduce gastrointestinal side effects or nausea, which is commonly seen in some patients in the first few weeks of treatment.| Q. Do the gastrointestinal side effects due to Alzepil 5mg Tablet persist for a long time?::: Gastrointestinal side effects may appear during the first few weeks of treatment with Alzepil 5mg Tablet. This can be minimized by taking Alzepil 5mg Tablet at bedtime and with food. Generally, these side effects are mild and disappear within a few weeks with continued treatment.| Q. How long does it take for Alzepil 5mg Tablet to start working?::: Within the first month of treatment with Alzepil 5mg Tablet, you may experience improvement in thinking and remembering (cognitive effect). However, it may take about 12 weeks to see the full benefits.| Q. When should Alzepil 5mg Tablet be stopped?::: Do not stop Alzepil 5mg Tablet without consulting your doctor. This medicine only helps to control your condition but does not cure it. Therefore, it may take several weeks to show benefits, so do not be discouraged if you do not see an improvement straight away. But, in case your condition starts worsening and you feel that it is no longer helping you, then you should consult a doctor before stopping it.| Q. For how long does Alzepil 5mg Tablet stay in your system?::: Alzepil 5mg Tablet gets removed from the body very slowly. It takes about two weeks or more for Alzepil 5mg Tablet to be completely removed from the system.| Q. Does Alzepil 5mg Tablet cause depression?::: No, Alzepil 5mg Tablet does not cause depression. If you are experiencing symptoms, then it could be due to existing Alzheimer’s disease.| Q. What if I take more than the prescribed dose of Alzepil 5mg Tablet?::: Taking more than the recommended dose of Alzepil 5mg Tablet may cause vomiting, increased sweating or saliva production, slow heartbeat, dizziness, difficulty in breathing, seizures or fits, weakness, low blood pressure, convulsions, and inability to control your bowel motions or passing of urine (incontinence). You should seek immediate help from a doctor or emergency service of a nearby hospital.| Q. I have been taking indomethacin for arthritis. Can I take Alzepil 5mg Tablet?::: Alzepil 5mg Tablet does not interfere with the working of indomethacin, but indomethacin individually increases the risk of stomach bleeding when taken for a long time. Therefore, if you experience any symptoms of stomach bleeding, consult your doctor immediately.| Q. Does Alzepil 5mg Tablet cause hallucinations?::: Hallucinations are a common side effect of Alzepil 5mg Tablet, though not everyone is affected. Other common psychiatric side effects include agitation, aggressive behavior, nightmares, and abnormal dreams.| Q. Who should not take Alzepil 5mg Tablet?::: Alzepil 5mg Tablet should not be taken by patients who have hypersensitivity to Alzepil 5mg Tablet hydrochloride, piperidine derivatives, or to any active ingredients used in the medicine. Also, it should not be used during pregnancy unless clearly necessary.| Q. Can it cause insomnia?::: Yes, insomnia (sleeplessness) is a common side effect of Alzepil 5mg Tablet. Dizziness and fainting can also be seen as common side effects. Though these side effects are common, they do not occur in everyone.",
        "how_it_works": "Memory loss in Alzheimer’s disease occurs due to disturbances of signal transmission in the brain. Alzepil 5mg Tablet is a cholinesterase inhibitor. It works by increasing the levels of a chemical messenger (acetylcholine) involved in transmmission of nerve signals. This improves memory and thinking.",
        "interaction": "Alzepil 5mg Tablet & Atropine 1% Eye Drop :  Concurrent use of Atropine and Donepezil should be avoided. | Alzepil 5mg Tablet & Topin Eye Drop :  Concurrent use of Atropine and Donepezil should be avoided. | Alzepil 5mg Tablet & Bellpino Atrin Eye Drop 1% :  Concurrent use of Atropine and Donepezil should be avoided. | Alzepil 5mg Tablet & Tropine 0.6mg Injection :  Concurrent use of Atropine and Donepezil should be avoided. | Alzepil 5mg Tablet & Bell Pino Atrin Eye Drop :  Concurrent use of Atropine and Donepezil should be avoided. | Alzepil 5mg Tablet & Atrop Eye Drop :  Concurrent use of Atropine and Donepezil should be avoided. | Alzepil 5mg Tablet & Atroped 0.01% Eye Drop :  Concurrent use of Atropine and Donepezil should be avoided. | Alzepil 5mg Tablet & Atro Eye Drop :  Concurrent use of Atropine and Donepezil should be avoided. | Alzepil 5mg Tablet & Mydrat-J Eye Drop :  Concurrent use of Atropine and Donepezil should be avoided. | Alzepil 5mg Tablet & Malano 0.3mg Injection :  Concurrent use of Atropine and Donepezil should be avoided.",
