        "qa": "Q. Can Piopill 30 Tablet cause weight gain?::: Piopill 30 Tablet commonly causes weight gain which may be dose-related. The reason for this weight gain could be fat accumulation. However, in heart failure patients it could be due to water retention in the body. Therefore, it is important to monitor weight in heart failure cases.| Q. Can Piopill 30 Tablet cause heart failure?::: Piopill 30 Tablet can cause fluid retention which may aggravate or speed up heart failure. The doctor usually starts with the lowest available dose and increases the dose gradually while treating patients who have at least one risk factor for heart failure (previous heart attack, coronary artery disease, elderly). Heart failure is more common when Piopill 30 Tablet is used with insulin.| Q. Can you take Piopill 30 Tablet and metformin together?::: Yes, Piopill 30 Tablet can be used with metformin where sufficient blood sugar management was not possible with metformin alone. This combination of medicines can be used in adult patients with type 2 diabetes mellitus and overweight patients with poor blood sugar control.| Q. What time of day should you take Piopill 30 Tablet?::: It is usually prescribed once daily and can be taken at any time of the day but preferably at the same time each day. It can be taken with or without food. You should take Piopill 30 Tablet exactly as prescribed by your doctor.| Q. How long do I need to take Piopill 30 Tablet? Can I stop the medicine for some time?::: Continue taking Piopill 30 Tablet as long as your doctor recommends taking it. Treatment for diabetes mellitus is long-term so you may have to take it lifelong. However, if you have to stop it then consult with your doctor who will suggest an alternative. Do not stop taking it without consulting your doctor as it may cause blood sugar levels to rise, which could be harmful to you.| Q. Does Piopill 30 Tablet affect liver?::: Yes, Piopill 30 Tablet may cause an increase in liver enzymes, and treatment with Piopill 30 Tablet should be stopped if liver enzymes increase. Hence, levels of liver enzymes should be periodically checked while on treatment with this medicine. Piopill 30 Tablet should not be prescribed to patients with liver disease.| Q. What kind of medicine is Piopill 30 Tablet? Is it like metformin?::: Piopill 30 Tablet belongs to the thiazolidinediones class of anti-diabetic medicines. It helps control blood sugar levels by improving how your body uses a hormone called insulin. This is done by helping your cells become more sensitive to the insulin your body makes.| Q. Can Piopill 30 Tablet cause bladder cancer?::: Piopill 30 Tablet may increase the risk of bladder cancer, though it is very rare. Immediately consult your doctor if you experience blood in your urine, pain when urinating or a sudden need to urinate, during treatment with this medicine. Piopill 30 Tablet should not be used in patients with a prior history of bladder cancer or having bladder cancer.",
        "how_it_works": "Piopill 30 Tablet is an anti-diabetic medication. It works by increasing the body's sensitivity to insulin, a natural substance that helps control blood sugar levels.",
        "interaction": "Piopill Tablet 30 & Keno 200mg Tablet :  Use of Pioglitazone and Trimethoprim should be avoided at the same time. | Piopill Tablet 30 & Tmp 300mg Tablet :  Use of Pioglitazone and Trimethoprim should be avoided at the same time. | Piopill Tablet 30 & Tabrol Syrup :  Use of Pioglitazone and Trimethoprim should be avoided at the same time. | Piopill Tablet 30 & Metstol 100mg Tablet :  Use of Pioglitazone and Trimethoprim should be avoided at the same time. | Piopill Tablet 30 & Bacstol Tablet :  Use of Pioglitazone and Trimethoprim should be avoided at the same time. | Piopill Tablet 30 & Omstat Tablet 10mg :  Use of Pioglitazone and Trimethoprim should be avoided at the same time. | Piopill Tablet 30 & Bacstol 200 Tablet :  Use of Pioglitazone and Trimethoprim should be avoided at the same time. | Piopill Tablet 30 & Amiur 5mg Tablet :  There is no significant interaction. But if higher doses of Amiloride are used along with Pioglitazone, it is recommended to monitor the blood glucose levels regularly. | Piopill Tablet 30 & Betasone 4mg Injection :  It is recommended to monitor the blood glucose level regularly as cases of high blood sugar levels have been seen in some patients. | Piopill Tablet 30 & Decdan B 4mg/ml Injection :  It is recommended to monitor the blood glucose level regularly as cases of high blood sugar levels have been seen in some patients.",
