        "qa": "Q. For how long does Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet stay in your system?::: On an average, Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet may stay in your system for 5-6 days. This duration varies from person to person. In some cases, it may stay for about 9-10 days.| Q. What happens if I stop taking Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet?::: Suddenly stopping Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet may cause non-stop seizures (called status epilepticus), which can endanger life. Do not stop taking the medicine without consulting your doctor. If required, your doctor will slowly reduce the dose before stopping it completely.| Q. What are the symptoms that occur if I take more than the recommended dose of Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet? Can I die from Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet overdose?::: Overdose of Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet may cause jerky movements of the eyes (nystagmus), unclear speech, loss of balance, tremor, muscle stiffness or weakness, nausea, vomiting, lightheadedness, fainting, blurred vision, slow and shallow breathing and even coma. Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet overdose can cause very low blood pressure and respiratory problems. As a result of this, the patient can even die.| Q. Who should avoid taking Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet?::: You should not take Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet if you have liver disease, especially if you have a history of developing a liver problem due to Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet. Also, patients taking Delavirdine (a medicine used in the treatment of HIV infection) should not take Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet. Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet may reduce the effectiveness of Delavirdine on HIV and the virus may also become resistant to Delavirdine. It is advised that you inform your doctor if you have any existing heart disorder before you receive Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet.| Q. Can I take Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet with ibuprofen?::: Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet can be taken with ibuprofen. No drug-drug interactions have been reported between the two. However, interactions can occur. Please consult your doctor before taking the two medicines together.| Q. What are the effects of Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet on children?::: The most common side effects related to Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet in children are jerky movements of the eyes (nystagmus) and overgrowth of the gums. In some children, Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet causes problems with thinking or behavior, mood change, slow or clumsy movements, or a loss of energy. Other side effects from high doses include unsteadiness in the feet and hands, sleepiness, and vomiting. These may be avoidable if the dose is increased slowly. These side effects quickly disappear when the dose is reduced.| Q. Does Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet cause weight gain?::: Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet has not been reported to cause weight gain. However, weight loss can occur with longer term use of a higher dose of Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet. Please consult your doctor if you experience weight gain after taking Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet.| Q. Does Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet make you sleepy?::: Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet can make you feel sleepy (sedation, somnolence, and drowsiness). Please consult your doctor if you feel very sleepy after taking Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet, especially during the first few weeks of treatment or following a dose increase. Talk to your doctor as you may be advised not to drive or use machines until it is established that your ability to perform such activities is not affected.| Q. Does Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet affect birth control?::: Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet does affect birth control. Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet can decrease the effect of oral contraceptives (birth control pills) which can make the contraceptive (birth control) effect unreliable. Please talk to your doctor if you are asked to take the two medicines together as you may need to use extra protection for birth control.",
        "how_it_works": "Lupin's Epilan 300mg Tablet is an antiepileptic medication. It controls seizures or fits by decreasing the abnormal and excessive activity of the nerve cells in the brain.",
        "interaction": "Tablet Lupin's Epilan 300mg & Fos-Aprepitant 125mg Tablet :  Concurrent use of Aprepitant and Phenytoin should be avoided. Blood levels of Aprepitant and effects of Aprepitant and Phenytoin are expected to be reduced. | Tablet Lupin's Epilan 300mg & Apriset 150mg Injection :  Concurrent use of Aprepitant and Phenytoin should be avoided. Blood levels of Aprepitant and effects of Aprepitant and Phenytoin are expected to be reduced. | Tablet Lupin's Epilan 300mg & Fosapine Injection 150mg :  Concurrent use of Aprepitant and Phenytoin should be avoided. Blood levels of Aprepitant and effects of Aprepitant and Phenytoin are expected to be reduced. | Tablet Lupin's Epilan 300mg & Aprepit Kit :  Concurrent use of Aprepitant and Phenytoin should be avoided. Blood levels of Aprepitant and effects of Aprepitant and Phenytoin are expected to be reduced. | Tablet Lupin's Epilan 300mg & Aprepep 125mg Capsule :  Concurrent use of Aprepitant and Phenytoin should be avoided. Blood levels of Aprepitant and effects of Aprepitant and Phenytoin are expected to be reduced. | Tablet Lupin's Epilan 300mg & Aprecap 150mg Injection :  Concurrent use of Aprepitant and Phenytoin should be avoided. Blood levels of Aprepitant and effects of Aprepitant and Phenytoin are expected to be reduced. | Tablet Lupin's Epilan 300mg & Regubeat 100mg Tablet :  Concurrent use of Disopyramide and Phenytoin should be avoided. Blood levels of Disopyramide are reduced by Phenytoin and may fall below therapeutic levels to control abnormal heart beat. | Tablet Lupin's Epilan 300mg & Norpace New Capsule :  Concurrent use of Disopyramide and Phenytoin should be avoided. Blood levels of Disopyramide are reduced by Phenytoin and may fall below therapeutic levels to control abnormal heart beat. | Tablet Lupin's Epilan 300mg & Norpace 100 Capsule :  Concurrent use of Disopyramide and Phenytoin should be avoided. Blood levels of Disopyramide are reduced by Phenytoin and may fall below therapeutic levels to control abnormal heart beat. | Tablet Lupin's Epilan 300mg & Nimulid Syrup :  Concurrent use of Nimesulide and Phenytoin should be avoided.",
