        "qa": "Q. How long does it take for Exiforce 100mg Tablet to work?::: The amount of time Exiforce 100mg Tablet takes to work varies from person to person, but it normally takes between half an hour and one hour. However, Exiforce 100mg Tablet may take longer to start working if you take it with a heavy meal. Its effect may last for about 3-4 hours.| Q. Can I get Exiforce 100mg Tablet without a prescription?::: No, you need a doctor's prescription to get Exiforce 100mg Tablet since it is a prescription medicine. Your doctor will prescribe it only if they judge that it would be beneficial for you.| Q. Can I take Exiforce 100mg Tablet as often as I want?::: No, do not take Exiforce 100mg Tablet for more than once a day. If you take more Exiforce 100mg Tablet than the recommended dose then you may experience an increase in side effects and their severity. These side effects include flushing, headache, muscle pain, stomach upset, allergic reactions and vision changes such as blurred vision. Contact your doctor if Exiforce 100mg Tablet does not help you to get an erection, or if your erection does not last long enough for you to complete sexual intercourse. | Q. When should I take Exiforce 100mg Tablet?::: Take Exiforce 100mg Tablet about 1 hour before you plan to have sex. Swallow the tablet whole with a glass of water. Inform your doctor if you feel the effect of Exiforce 100mg Tablet is too strong or too weak.| Q. Can I take Exiforce 100mg Tablet for premature ejaculation?::: No, Exiforce 100mg Tablet is not known to have any beneficial effects in treating premature ejaculation. It is used for the treatment of erectile dysfunction. | Q. Why is the use of Exiforce 100mg Tablet contraindicated with nitrates?::: Use of Exiforce 100mg Tablet is harmful for patients taking nitrates or blood pressure-lowering medicines as their combined use can cause a severe fall in blood pressure, which can also result in death. However, if these medicines are to be taken together then it is advised to keep a time gap of 24 hours between the intake of Penegra and blood pressure-lowering medicines.| Q. Why does Exiforce 100mg Tablet cause a fall in blood pressure (hypotension)?::: Exiforce 100mg Tablet has the property of relaxing the smooth muscle of the blood vessels and widening them which can cause a fall in blood pressure (hypotension). So, when used with blood pressure lowering medicines or nitrates, it can cause a severe fall in blood pressure, which could be fatal. Exiforce 100mg Tablet should not be taken if you are taking nitrates for chest pain or you have a history of heart attack or stroke in the past 6 months.| Q. Can I take Exiforce 100mg Tablet in my twenties?::: Yes, if prescribed by your doctor then Exiforce 100mg Tablet can be taken in your twenties.| Q. Does Exiforce 100mg Tablet increase blood pressure?::: No, Exiforce 100mg Tablet is not associated with an increase in blood pressure. However, it can cause a decrease in blood pressure especially if taken with other blood pressure-lowering medications. Please consult your doctor before taking Exiforce 100mg Tablet with any other medicine.| Q. Is Exiforce 100mg Tablet safe to use in patients with diabetes?::: Yes, if prescribed by your doctor then Exiforce 100mg Tablet is safe to use in patients with diabetes.| Q. Does Exiforce 100mg Tablet affect fertility?::: No, Exiforce 100mg Tablet does not affect fertility, neither negatively nor positively.| Q. Does Exiforce 100mg Tablet affect sperm?::: Exiforce 100mg Tablet does not affect sperm count or its health. It is a medicine that is used to treat erectile dysfunction.| Q. Can I drink alcohol while on Exiforce 100mg Tablet?::: Drinking alcohol can temporarily impair your ability to get an erection. To get the maximum benefit from Exiforce 100mg Tablet, it is advised to not drink excessive amounts of alcohol before taking Exiforce 100mg Tablet.| Q. Can I take Exiforce 100mg Tablet as often as I want?::: No, do not take Exiforce 100mg Tablet for more than once a day. If you take more Exiforce 100mg Tablet than the recommended dose then you may experience an increase in side effects and their severity. These side effects include flushing, headache, muscle pain, stomach upset, allergic reactions and vision changes such as blurred vision. Contact your doctor if Exiforce 100mg Tablet does not help you to get an erection, or if your erection does not last long enough for you to complete sexual intercourse. | Q. When should I take Exiforce 100mg Tablet?::: Take Exiforce 100mg Tablet about 1 hour before you plan to have sex. Swallow the tablet whole with a glass of water. Inform your doctor if you feel the effect of Exiforce 100mg Tablet is too strong or too weak.| Q. Can I drink alcohol while on Exiforce 100mg Tablet?::: Drinking alcohol can temporarily impair your ability to get an erection. To get the maximum benefit from Exiforce 100mg Tablet, it is advised to not drink excessive amounts of alcohol before taking Exiforce 100mg Tablet.",
