        "qa": "Q. How does Flohale 50mcg Inhaler work?::: Flohale 50mcg Inhaler works by decreasing the inflammation caused by allergies. It reduces inflammation by blocking the release of certain natural substances that cause allergic symptoms such as swelling, redness and pain.| Q. How long does Flohale 50mcg Inhaler take to start working? ::: The time Flohale 50mcg Inhaler requires to start working differs from person to person. However, you may get relief within 8 hours of starting Flohale 50mcg Inhaler. It may even take several days before you see maximum benefits. In order to improve your symptoms faster, it is important to take the medicine regularly to gain maximum benefit from the medicine.| Q. My friend developed a severe allergic reaction when she started Flohale 50mcg Inhaler. Could it be due to Flohale 50mcg Inhaler even though it is used for allergy purposes?::: In very rare cases, Flohale 50mcg Inhaler can cause serious allergic reactions such as rash, hives, breathing difficulty, swelling of the face, throat and tongue. It may also cause low blood pressure which may further cause lightheadedness and the patient may even faint. If these symptoms occur, you should immediately contact your doctor because such allergic reactions can be life threatening.| Q. My brother developed chickenpox while using Flohale 50mcg Inhaler. Can Flohale 50mcg Inhaler be responsible for chickenpox? What should be done?::: Yes, it could be possible. The reason being, Flohale 50mcg Inhaler is a corticosteroid, which weakens the immune system of the body, making the body prone to infections such as chicken pox. You should immediately stop the medication and contact the doctor. The doctor may consider treating it with antiviral agents.| Q. What is Flohale 50mcg Inhaler? What is it used for?::: Flohale 50mcg Inhaler belongs to a group of medicines called steroids, also known as corticosteroids. Flohale 50mcg Inhaler is used to treat various allergic skin conditions such as eczema and atopic dermatitis. Flohale 50mcg Inhaler effectively reduces symptoms associated with such conditions such as swelling, itching and redness.",
        "how_it_works": "Flohale 50mcg Inhaler is a steroid. It prevents the cells in the lungs and breathing passages from releasing chemical messengers that cause inflammation (swelling) of the airways. This makes breathing easier.",
