        "safety_advise": "- Alcohol : UNSAFE  It is unsafe to consume alcohol with Drospas M 80mg/250mg Tablet. | - Pregnancy : CONSULT YOUR DOCTOR  Drospas M 80mg/250mg Tablet may be unsafe to use during pregnancy. Although there are limited studies in humans, animal studies have shown harmful effects on the developing baby. Your doctor will weigh the benefits and any potential risks before prescribing it to you. Please consult your doctor. | - Breast feeding : CONSULT YOUR DOCTOR  Information regarding the use of Drospas M 80mg/250mg Tablet during breastfeeding is not available. Please consult your doctor. | - Driving : UNSAFE  Drospas M 80mg/250mg Tablet may cause side effects which could affect your ability to drive.As Drospas M 80mg/250mg Tablet may cause vertigo. | - Kidney : CAUTION  Drospas M 80mg/250mg Tablet should be used with caution in patients with kidney disease. Dose adjustment of Drospas M 80mg/250mg Tablet may be needed. Please consult your doctor.Use of Drospas M 80mg/250mg Tablet is not recommended in patients with severe kidney disease. | - Liver : CAUTION  Drospas M 80mg/250mg Tablet should be used with caution in patients with liver disease. Dose adjustment of Drospas M 80mg/250mg Tablet may be needed. Please consult your doctor.Use of Drospas M 80mg/250mg Tablet is not recommended in patients with severe liver disease. Regular monitoring of liver function tests is advisable while the patient is taking this medicine.",
