        "qa": "Q. What is Sunraz 40mg Tablet used for?::: Sunraz 40mg Tablet is used for the treatment of peptic ulcer disease, reflux esophagitis or gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD). Sunraz 40mg Tablet prevents acidity associated with use of painkillers. It is also used to treat a disease associated with excessive acid production in the stomach known as Zollinger Ellison syndrome (ZES). It works by reducing the amount of acid made by your stomach and thus relieves your symptoms.| Q. How long does it take for Sunraz 40mg Tablet to work?::: You should start to feel better within 2 to 3 days. It may take up to 4 weeks for Sunraz 40mg Tablet to work properly so you may still have some symptoms during this time.| Q. Is a single dose of Sunraz 40mg Tablet sufficient?::: No, a single dose may not be sufficient. However, with only a few doses of Sunraz 40mg Tablet you may get relief with the symptoms. Sunraz 40mg Tablet is usually needed only for a short term or upto 2 weeks for heartburn, indigestion, acid reflux. However, if need arises, such as for treating peptic ulcer disease and Zollinger Ellison syndrome (ZES), Sunraz 40mg Tablet may be prescribed for a long term duration as well. Please consult your doctor if you do not feel better even after taking Sunraz 40mg Tablet regularly for 2 weeks as prescribed.| Q. Is Sunraz 40mg Tablet safe?::: Yes, Sunraz 40mg Tablet is relatively safe. Most of the people who take Sunraz 40mg Tablet do not get a side effect. It is advised to be taken as directed by the doctor for maximum benefits.| Q. Can I take Sunraz 40mg Tablet for a long term?::: Sunraz 40mg Tablet is usually prescribed for short-term use only. However, if the need arises, such as for treating peptic ulcer disease, ZE syndrome, etc. Sunraz 40mg Tablet may be prescribed for a long-term duration as well. Long-term use may carry an increased risk for side effects and must be discussed with the doctor. Please use Sunraz 40mg Tablet as advised by your doctor and under their supervision.| Q. What are the long term side effects of Sunraz 40mg Tablet?::: If Sunraz 40mg Tablet is used for more than 3 months, certain long-term side effects may be seen. The most important of these is low magnesium levels in your blood which may make you feel tired, confused, dizzy, shaky, or dizzy. You may also have muscle twitches or irregular heartbeat. If the use is further prolonged for more than a year, you may have an increased risk of bone fractures, stomach infections, and vitamin B12 deficiency. Vitamin B12 deficiency can make you anemic, as a result of which you may feel more tired, weak, or pale. Additionally, you may have palpitations, shortness of breath, lightheadedness, indigestion, loss of appetite, flatulence (gas), or nerve problems such as numbness, tingling, and problem in walking.| Q. What is the best time to take Sunraz 40mg Tablet?::: Usually, Sunraz 40mg Tablet is taken once a day, first thing in the morning. If you take Sunraz 40mg Tablet twice a day, take 1 dose in the morning and 1 dose in the evening. The tablets should be swallowed whole (remember not to be chewed or crushed) and taken at least 1 hour before a meal with some water.| Q. Can I stop taking Sunraz 40mg Tablet if I feel better?::: If you have been taking Sunraz 40mg Tablet for a long time. Stopping it abruptly may lead to increased acid production, thereby worsening your symptoms. Therefore, you must discuss any dose changes or if you wish to come off Sunraz 40mg Tablet.| Q. Does Sunraz 40mg Tablet cause weight gain?::: Although rare but long-term treatment with Sunraz 40mg Tablet may cause weight gain. The reason could be the relief from reflux symptoms which could make you eat more. Consult your doctor for any weight-related concern.| Q. Can I take alcohol with Sunraz 40mg Tablet?::: No, alcohol intake is not advised with Sunraz 40mg Tablet. Alcohol itself does not affect the working of Sunraz 40mg Tablet, but it can increase the acid production. This may further cause worsening of your symptoms.| Q. Can I take antacids along with Sunraz 40mg Tablet?::: Yes, you can take antacids along with Sunraz 40mg Tablet. Take it 2 hours before or after you take Sunraz 40mg Tablet.| Q. What dietary changes should I make to get relief from acidity?::: Sunraz 40mg Tablet is best taken 1 hour before a meal. You should avoid spicy and fatty foods while taking this medicine. You must refrain from caffeinated drinks such as tea, coffee and cola. Alcohol intake should also be avoided as it may worsen your symptoms.| Q. Are painkillers safe to take along with Sunraz 40mg Tablet?::: Yes, it is safe to take painkillers along with Sunraz 40mg Tablet. Sunraz 40mg Tablet prevents acidity and stomach ulcers associated with the intake of painkillers. Sunraz 40mg Tablet is taken 1 hour before a meal. On the other hand, painkillers are usually taken with, or after a meal to avoid stomach upset.",
        "how_it_works": "Sunraz 40mg Tablet is a proton pump inhibitor (PPI). It works by reducing the amount of acid in the stomach which in turn relieves acid-related indigestion and heartburn.",
        "interaction": "Sunraz 40mg Tablet & Atazor 200mg Capsule :  Concurrent use of Atazanavir and Pantoprazole should be avoided. | Sunraz 40mg Tablet & Atazor 300 Capsule :  Concurrent use of Atazanavir and Pantoprazole should be avoided. | Sunraz 40mg Tablet & Atavir 300mg Capsule :  Concurrent use of Atazanavir and Pantoprazole should be avoided. | Sunraz 40mg Tablet & Virataz 300mg Capsule :  Concurrent use of Atazanavir and Pantoprazole should be avoided. | Sunraz 40mg Tablet & Cilodoc 100 Tablet :  Concurrent use of Cilostazol and Pantoprazole should be avoided. | Sunraz 40mg Tablet & Stiloz 50 Tablet :  Concurrent use of Cilostazol and Pantoprazole should be avoided. | Sunraz 40mg Tablet & CILESTA 50MG TABLET :  Concurrent use of Cilostazol and Pantoprazole should be avoided. | Sunraz 40mg Tablet & CILESTA 100MG TABLET :  Concurrent use of Cilostazol and Pantoprazole should be avoided. | Sunraz 40mg Tablet & Cletus 50mg Tablet :  Concurrent use of Cilostazol and Pantoprazole should be avoided. | Sunraz 40mg Tablet & Cletus 100mg Tablet :  Concurrent use of Cilostazol and Pantoprazole should be avoided.",
